---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LegalHeader from "../../components/LegalHeader.astro";
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from "../../i18n/ui";

const lastUpdated = "Last updated: 13 May 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Legal Notice"
  description="Legal notice for the retropal.fr site and the Retro Pal app. Publisher, host, contact, and open-source licenses."
>
  <div class="page-shell legal-page">
    <LegalHeader
      kicker="Legal Notice"
      title="Legal notice"
      updated={lastUpdated}
    />

    <article class="prose">
      <h2>Publisher</h2>
      <dl class="meta-list">
        <dt>Trading name</dt>
        <dd>Antoine Ghiassi — Micro-enterprise (auto-entrepreneur, France)</dd>

        <dt>SIRET</dt>
        <dd>104 692 538 00010</dd>

        <dt>Address</dt>
        <dd>35 rue Proudhon<br />75012 Paris<br />France</dd>

        <dt>Email</dt>
        <dd><a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a></dd>

        <dt>Publication director</dt>
        <dd>Antoine Ghiassi</dd>
      </dl>

      <h2>Host</h2>
      <p>The retropal.fr site is hosted by:</p>
      <dl class="meta-list">
        <dt>Company</dt>
        <dd>Cloudflare, Inc.</dd>

        <dt>Address</dt>
        <dd>101 Townsend Street<br />San Francisco, CA 94107<br />United States</dd>

        <dt>Website</dt>
        <dd><a href="https://www.cloudflare.com" rel="noopener">www.cloudflare.com</a></dd>
      </dl>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        All elements making up the retropal.fr site and the Retro Pal application (texts, graphics,
        logo, visual identity, specific source code) are the exclusive property of the publisher,
        unless explicitly stated otherwise. Any reproduction, representation, modification, or
        exploitation of all or part of these elements, by any process and on any medium, is forbidden
        without prior written authorization from the publisher, and constitutes counterfeiting
        punishable under articles L.335-2 et seq. of the French Intellectual Property Code.
      </p>

      <h2>Open-source software used</h2>
      <p>
        The Retro Pal application incorporates the following open-source components:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>mGBA</strong> — emulator for Game Boy, Game Boy Color and Game Boy Advance, under
          the Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0).
          Source code available at <a href="https://mgba.io" rel="noopener">mgba.io</a>.
          Source code not modified.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>melonDS</strong> — emulator for Nintendo DS, under the GNU General Public License
          v3.0 (GPL-3.0).
          Source code available at <a href="https://melonds.kuribo64.net" rel="noopener">melonds.kuribo64.net</a>.
          Source code not modified.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The application fully complies with the terms of these licenses. Complete license text is
        available at the URLs above as well as inside the app, in Settings → Licenses.
      </p>

      <h2>Fonts</h2>
      <p>
        The site uses the VT323, Newsreader, and JetBrains Mono typefaces, distributed under the
        SIL Open Font License 1.1. They are self-hosted on our own servers and do not load any
        third-party resource.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party trademarks</h2>
      <p>
        Game Boy, Game Boy Color, Game Boy Advance, and Nintendo DS are registered trademarks of
        Nintendo Co., Ltd. Apple, App Store and iPhone are registered trademarks of Apple Inc.
        These trademarks are mentioned on this site and in the application only descriptively, to
        indicate technical compatibility of Retro Pal. The publisher of Retro Pal is not in any
        way affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by Nintendo or Apple.
      </p>

      <h2>Consumer mediation</h2>
      <p>
        In accordance with articles L.611-1 et seq. of the French Consumer Code, any consumer has
        the right to free recourse to a consumer mediator for the amicable resolution of a dispute
        with a professional. However, since most app-related purchases are made through the Apple
        App Store platform, disputes relating to a purchase should first be brought to Apple via
        <a href="https://support.apple.com/billing" rel="noopener">support.apple.com/billing</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Personal data</h2>
      <p>
        The (lack of) processing of personal data is detailed in our
        <a href="/en/privacy">Privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For any question regarding the site, the app or this notice:
        <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page { padding-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem); }
  .meta-list {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem 1.5rem;
    margin-block: 1rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .meta-list dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    padding-top: 0.3rem;
  }
  .meta-list dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .meta-list { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.15rem; }
    .meta-list dd { margin-bottom: 0.85rem; }
  }
</style>
